<TITLE> Jamaluddin's family to sue Babar, 4 others </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 2 (bdnews24.com)  The family of slain Chittagong businessman and BNP leader Jamaluddin Chowdhury has decided to sue former state minister for home Lutfozzaman Babar and four others, including two policemen, for the murder. Nazma Akhter Khanam, wife of Jamaluddin, said they would sue five people including Babar for getting the police to not press murder charges against former BNP lawmaker Sarwar Jamal Nizam and his brother Maruf Nizam. The Nizam brothers, investigation officer of the case CID inspector Anwar Hossain and CID ASP Hamidul Haque, who investigated the case in the second phase, would be the accused in the case, Jamaluddin's wife told bdnews24.com by telephone Saturday. bdnews24.c
